8 AS INTRODUCED
9 A Concurrent Resolution commemorating April 14, 2025,
as Route 66 Day in the State of Oklahoma; recognizing
10 the historic and cultural importance of U.S. Route
66; and directing distribution.
11
12
13 WHEREAS, U.S. Route 66, also known as the “Mother Road”, was
14 established in 1926 and served as a vital artery of American
15 transportation, running from Chicago, Illinois, to Santa Monica,
16 California, with over 400 miles traversing the State of Oklahoma;
17 and
18 WHEREAS, Route 66 played a pivotal role in the migration west
19 during the Dust Bowl era, providing a path to opportunity and
20 survival for countless Oklahomans; and
21 WHEREAS, the communities along Route 66 in Oklahoma have long
22 served as vibrant centers of commerce, culture, and hospitality,
23 offering a unique blend of small-town charm, urban energy, and
24 scenic beauty; and
