1 WHEREAS, the route has significantly contributed to Oklahoma’s
2 tourism industry, drawing travelers from across the nation and
3 around the world who seek to experience its vintage landmarks,
4 historic motels, neon signs, and iconic diners; and
5 WHEREAS, Oklahoma’s rich tribal heritage is deeply woven into
6 the Route 66 experience, with tribal nations preserving and sharing
7 cultural traditions, stories, art, and enterprises along the
8 historic highway; and
9 WHEREAS, Route 66 has become a symbol of Oklahoma’s diverse
10 identity, celebrating our state’s legacy of resilience, creativity,
11 and community spirit.
12 NOW, THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED BY THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES
13 OF THE 1ST SESSION OF THE 60TH OKLAHOMA LEGISLATURE, THE SENATE
14 CONCURRING THEREIN:
15 THAT the Oklahoma Legislature does hereby commemorate April 11,
16 2025, as Route 66 Day, honoring its historical significance,
17 cultural richness, and ongoing impact on the State of Oklahoma.
18 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED, that a copy of this resolution be
19 distributed to the Oklahoma Tourism and Recreation Department and
20 the Oklahoma Historical Society for appropriate observance and
21 celebration.
